Rating: 3
I found a sale on turkey scallopini and, because it was so inexpensive, I bought it UP...then I tried to find some recipes..that wasn't successful but this recipe was a dream come true!!! It is tender and it is not dry -- beautiful! I didn't have dried bread crumbs so I substituted cornmeal...oooh very yum!

Rating: 4
I've used this recipe frequently, and typically serve it with the Chive Jive New Potatoes recipe (also on this site - Bon Appetit '96) to keep with the low fat theme. Only changes are to first dredge the cutlets in flour, and sometimes use panko for crumbs. Love the vinaigrette for the greens and use it often with side salads to accompany quiches or other light/simple dishes. It's a perfect way to lightly dress a salad.

Rating: 3
Tasty and easy. Dredge the cutlets in flour before putting them in the eggwash. That way the crumbs adhere much better.

