Rating: 3
Simple and delicious. I used fresh rosemary ( 1 1/2 tsp or so) and a bit more parmesan than it called for. The turkey was flavorful and tender -- just delicious. The salad dressing was also quite tasty and took no effort to make. I used a fresh orange and squeezed a tblsp or so of juice into the mix. It was so good to have a fresh, chemical-free dressing for the salad. It's a wonder to me why anyone would buy a balsamic vinagrette in a bottle.